window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>From Linda Castillo, the </b><b><i>New York Times</i></b><b> best-selling author of </b><b><i>A Gathering of Secrets</i></b><b>, comes a new Kate Burkholder short mystery, </b><b><i>In Plain Sight: </i></b><b>a story of star-crossed love and murder in Amish country. </b></p> <p>Seventeen-year-old Amish boy Noah Kline is struck by a car as he walks alongside a dark country road late one night in Painters Mill. Seriously injured, he lapses into a coma.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>Initially, Chief of Police Kate Burkholder believes it’s a straightforward hit-and-run, a driver that panicked and fled. But evidence soon emerges that the incident wasn’t accidental at all - and Kate uncovers a story of teenage passion and jealousy that may have led to attempted murder.</p>"; 
